<p>The Tidewater shirt by Tom Beckbe is what happens when rugged, outdoor performance meets a refined, coastal sensibility. It’s the kind of piece that feels just as natural on the lake as it does on a sun-drenched deck. The magic lies in the exclusive 2.8-ounce cotton-nylon blend. It’s ultra-lightweight and engineered with enough spandex for a flattering, flexible fit that moves with you. Most importantly, it delivers UPF 30+ sun protection, shielding you from harmful rays. It’s also incredibly lightweight and quick-drying. For anyone who has been waiting for an outdoor shirt that actually looks as good as it protects, the search ends here. </p>



